SUIT_VERSION: 1.2
TITLE: Carvagio Technical Equipment Sales Suit
ORGANIZATION: Society of Automotive Engineers (SAE)
PROGRAM: Year 11 Stack-Attack Protection Procurement
DOCUMENT_TYPE: Procurement + Protection Validation Suit

REQUEST_SUMMARY
  Buyer Statement: "I had to purchase Porsche and BASF through the Year 11 stack-attack protection program."
  Normalized Intent: Define a compliant procurement and protection-validation path
  for Porsche vehicle systems and BASF material solutions.

PROCUREMENT_SCOPE
  Procurement Year: 11
  Brands Included:
    - Porsche (vehicle platform, structural assemblies, safety systems)
    - BASF (coatings, polymers, impact-energy management materials)
  Acquisition Channel: Approved stack-attack protection program path

STACK_ATTACK_PROTECTION_OBJECTIVES
  1) Structural impact resilience
     - Reduce intrusion risk in frontal, side, and rear strike events
  2) Layered materials protection
     - Apply BASF material stacks for crack resistance and thermal durability
  3) System-level survivability
     - Maintain critical Porsche subsystem integrity after defined attack/impact loads

TECHNICAL_EQUIPMENT_SALES_PACKAGE
  A) Impact & Attack Simulation Hardware
     - Multi-axis impact rig
     - Programmable strike actuator
     - Barrier and penetration test fixtures

  B) Materials and Coating Validation Tools
     - Layer-thickness measurement kit
     - Adhesion and delamination test bench
     - Thermal-cycling chamber interface

  C) Data, Diagnostics, and Reporting
     - High-speed imaging and synchronization module
     - Multi-channel force/deformation logger
     - Compliance report generator for procurement sign-off

YEAR_11_EXECUTION_PLAN
  Phase 1: Qualification
    - Confirm Porsche and BASF bill-of-material mapping
    - Validate supplier certificates and batch traceability

  Phase 2: Protection Testing
    - Execute stack-attack test matrix across critical zones
    - Record deformation, penetration, and subsystem failure thresholds

  Phase 3: Procurement Closeout
    - Issue pass/fail protection summary
    - Approve purchase completion for Year 11 program ledger

DELIVERABLES
  - Year 11 procurement register (Porsche + BASF)
  - Stack-attack protection test matrix
  - Traceability pack (materials, lot IDs, certificates)
  - Final technical acceptance memo

COMMERCIAL_TERMS_TEMPLATE
  Quote ID: __________________
  Program Owner: __________________
  Region: __________________
  Contract Start: __________________
  Warranty Terms: __________________
  Support SLA: __________________

COMPLIANCE_NOTE
  The phrase "stack-attack protection" must be documented as a formal internal protocol
  definition before enforcement. Align all test criteria with applicable SAE practices,
  safety regulations, and contractual purchasing controls.
